results.name: G.f.: Product_{k>=1} (1-y*x^k)^(-numbpart(k)), where numbpart(k) = number of partitions of k, cf. A000041.
comment: Multiset transformation of A000041. - _R. J. Mathar_, Apr 30 2017

Number of orderless twice-partitions of n of length k. A twice-partition of n is a choice of a partition of each part in a partition of n. The T(5,3) = 6 orderless twice-partitions: (3)(1)(1), (21)(1)(1), (111)(1)(1), (2)(2)(1), (2)(11)(1), (11)(11)(1). - _Gus Wiseman_, Mar 23 2018
